Auto-generated Cargo dependency lockfile pinning exact versions and checksums for the whole workspace; not hand-edited — regenerate via `cargo build`/`cargo update` rather than modifying directly.

Confirms the workspace crates: `ctx-core` (no deps), `ctx-context`, `ctx-cage`, `ctx-verify` (all clap + serde + serde_json + thiserror), and `ctx-scan`/`ctx-summarize`, which additionally depend on `ignore` (gitignore-aware file walking) and `sha2` (used only by `ctx-scan`, for content hashing). `ctx-summarize` is a dependency of `ctx-scan`, not the reverse.

Notable indirect dependencies worth knowing about if a build breaks: `zmij` is pulled in by `serde_json` 1.0.149 (an unusual transitive name, not a typo); `clap`'s derive macro path brings in `syn`/`quote`/`proc-macro2`/`heck`; `ignore` pulls `crossbeam-deque`/`walkdir`/`globset` for parallel directory traversal. Editing any workspace member's `Cargo.toml` dependencies requires regenerating this file — manual edits will be overwritten and can desync from the actual dependency graph.